API Endpoint Specification
Endpoint: POST /auth/signup
Create user account
Request spec: (body)
{
“email”: Integer,
“password”: String,
“first_name”: String,
“last_name”: String,
...
}
Response spec:
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : {
“token” : String,
“first_name”: String,
“last_name”: String,
“email”: String,
...
}
}
Endpoint: POST /auth/signin
Login a user
Request spec: (body)
{
“email”: Integer,
“password”: String,
...
}
Response spec:
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : {
© Andela Confidential
“token” : String,
“first_name”: String,
“last_name”: String,
“email”: String,
...
}
}
Endpoint: POST /trips
Create a trip.
Request spec: (header)
{
“token”: String,
...
}
Response spec: (body)
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : {
“trip_id” : Integer,
“seating_capacity” : Integer,
“origin” : String,
”destination”: String,
“trip_date” : Date,
“fare” : Float,
...
}
}
Endpoint: GET /trips/<:trip-id>
Get a specific trip.
Request spec: (header)
{
“token”: String,
...
}
Response spec: (body)
{
“status”:“success”,
“data”:{
    “trip_id”:Integer,
“seating_capacity”:Integer,
“origin”:String

”destiatio”:String,
“trip_date”:Date,
“fare”:loat,
...
}
}
