Endpoint: PATCH /trips/<:trip-id>/cancel
Cancel a trip.
Request spec: (header)
{
“token”: String,
...
}
Response spec:
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : {
“message” : “Trip cancelled successfully”,
...
}
}
Endpoint: POST /bookings
Book a seat on a trip
Request spec: (header)
{
“token”: String,
...
}
Response spec:
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : {
“booking_id” : Integer,
“bus_license_number” : String,
© Andela Confidential
“trip_date”: Date,
“first_name”: String,
“last_name”: String,
“user_email”: String,
...
}
}
Endpoint: GET /bookings
View all bookings. An Admin can see all bookings, while user can see all of his/her
bookings.
Request spec: (header)
{
“token”: String,
...
}
Response spec:
{
“status” : “success”,
“data” : [
{
“booking_id” : Integer,
“bus_license_number” : String,
